<webwork-reps version="2" webwork2_major_version="2" webwork2_minor_version="20" xml:id="extracted-section-solving-rational-equations-10-10-28" assembly-id="section-solving-rational-equations-10-10-28">
  <static seed="1463" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalEquations/solveRationalEquations70.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve the equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ {\frac{t-7}{t+5}-\frac{8}{t+7}} = 5 }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="34" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left\{-11,-6\right\}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To get rid of fractions, we multiply each term in this equation by the common denominator, which is <m>{\left(t+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+7\right)}</m> in this example.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \amp {\frac{t-7}{t+5}-\frac{8}{t+7}} = 5 \\
   \amp {\frac{t-7}{t+5}\mathopen{}\left(t+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+7\right)-\frac{8}{t+7}\mathopen{}\left(t+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+7\right)} ={5\mathopen{}\left(t+5\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+7\right)} \\
   \amp {\left(t-7\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+7\right)-8\mathopen{}\left(t+5\right)} = {5\mathopen{}\left(t^{2}+12t+35\right)} \\
   \amp {t^{2}-49-8t-40} = {5t^{2}+60t+175} \\
   \amp {t^{2}-8t-89} = {5t^{2}+60t+175} \\
   \amp {t^{2}-8t-89-5t^{2}-60t-175} = 0 \\
   \amp {-\left(4t^{2}+68t+264\right)} = 0 \\
   \amp {-4\mathopen{}\left(t^{2}+17t+66\right)} = 0 \\
   \amp {-4\mathopen{}\left(t+11\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+6\right)} = 0 \\
   \amp {t+11}=0 \:\: or\:\: {t+6}=0 \\
   \amp t=-11 \:\: or\:\: t=-6
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p><alert>Checking</alert></p>
<p>We must check solutions when we solve rational equations. In the original equation, both denominators cannot be <m>0</m>. We set them to <m>0</m>, so we can find out what values to exclude from the solution set.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \amp t+5 = 0 \amp \;\amp  t+7=0 \\
   \amp t=-5 \amp \;\amp  t=-7
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>We must exclude <m>-5</m> and <m>-7</m> from the solution set, so the final solution is <m>t=-11</m> and <m>t=-6</m>.</p>
</solution>
